dt-option.default:
        The default value for the `-init searchPanes.minRows` paramater is `1`. When this default value is in place it will mean that columns with only 1 unique value will not have a pane built. This makes sense as there is no point searching a column for the only value that is present as it will not affect search results.


        As standard columns must have at least 2 different values present to have a pane displayed, although this is also affected by `-init searchPanes.thershold` and `-init columns.searchPanes.threshold`.

        By setting the `-init searchPanes.minRows` option to a different `-type integer` value, the number of different values in the columns must be greater than this value.





$(document).ready(function() {
    var dt = $('#example').DataTable( {
        searchPanes: {
            minRows:10
        }
    });
});



-init searchPanes.threshold
-init columns.searchPanes.threshold
-init columns.searchPanes.show
